  </advanced_techniques>

  <detection>
    - Monitor for debugging attachment
    - Detect jailbreak indicators
    - Check for Frida/Cycript presence
    - Validate code signing
    - Implement runtime integrity checks
  </detection>

  <validation>
    - Successfully instrument running app
    - Extract keychain contents
    - Bypass authentication controls
    - Access protected files
    - Document insecure data storage
  </validation>

  <pro_tips>
    - checkra1n works on A11 and below (hardware-based)
    - frida-ios-dump decrypts App Store apps automatically
    - Keychain persists after app uninstall - check for leftovers
    - Backups may contain data protection class None files
    - App Extensions have different entitlements - check each
    - WKWebView is sandboxed unlike deprecated UIWebView
  </pro_tips>

  <remember>iOS security is layered - code signing, sandboxing, data protection, keychain. Each layer must be tested. Jailbreaking bypasses most restrictions, enabling complete application analysis. Focus on how the app handles secrets, implements authentication, and protects sensitive data at rest and in transit.</remember>
</vulnerability_guide>
